  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of this study is to identify and quantify circulating tumor markers, which are
      associated with the presence of tumors. The current imaging available does not allow
      specificity of tumor size as it relates to pseudoprogression (a temporary enlargement or
      &quot;swelling&quot; of the tumor after treatment before it shrinks). Our hope is that CTCs will
      provide a more accurate description of tumor state for high grade glioma patients.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
